This paper deals with the design of contracts for spectrum reservation in TV white space networks, which involves issues related to network infrastructure, information theory, game theory, cryptography, and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
